history.content:
I have no specific experience with the company involved, but in general interviewers tend to go over 2 algorithm/Data Structure based questions, as well as general questions about your resume, experience, projects you worked on, etc.

As for preparation, do some practice interview questions, and make sure to write actual code for them (most interviewers don't want complete pseudocode); it's also a good idea to keep your resume handy to review what you've written for a particular project/experience, so you can build on that when asked about it.

Hello,

I have a phone call interview for a software engineering internship opportunity for MarkLogic on Wednesday.

I am wondering if anyone know what kind of questions they will ask? and how should I prepare for it?

Thank you
